<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Vended laundry service</p>
    <h2>Every hour a coin laundry is down is revenue gone. We treat vended uptime as the priority it is.</h2>

    <p>Coin laundry, also called vended laundry, is the self-service laundromat where customers pay per cycle. 24/7 operation, 5 to 15 cycles per machine per day, frequent abuse from foreign objects in coin slots, occasional vandalism, lint accumulation from mixed loads. Different service profile from on-premise laundry (OPL) and very different from industrial contract laundry. The operator's revenue is per-cycle, so every machine down is direct lost revenue, and that's the framing we work with.</p>

    <p>Our techs service the full vended laundry lineup across LA County, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>Speed Queen</strong> ZWN432, SF35, SF50 (Alliance Laundry, dominant US laundromat brand). <strong>Huebsch</strong> HC30, HC50 (Alliance Laundry value tier, sister to Speed Queen, slight cost advantage). <strong>Maytag Commercial Laundry</strong> MAT20PD, MAT50PD (Whirlpool Corp, common at chain laundromats). <strong>Continental Girbau Vended Series</strong> (Spanish independent, premium vended).</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. <strong>BHGS #A49573</strong> license. <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410</strong>. <strong>CSLB C-20 HVAC</strong> plus <strong>CSLB C-38 Refrigeration</strong> scope for adjacent gas-dryer and HVAC work in laundromat venues. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. Parent: <a href="/commercial/washer-repair/">commercial washer repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top vended-laundry repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Coin mechanism jam.</strong> Foreign objects (paper clips, washers, tokens, occasional vandalism). Clear the jam, inspect the slide and acceptor. $200 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Card reader / card-tap system failure.</strong> Modern systems (Speed Queen Quantum Touch, Huebsch eCommerce, integrated CCI and ESD). Cable, firmware, controller integration diagnostic. $640 to $1,100 replacement at year 4 to 6.</li>
      <li><strong>Door interlock switch.</strong> 5 to 15 cycles per day plus customer abuse means high cycle count wear. $260 to $420.</li>
      <li><strong>Drain pump.</strong> Heavy lint from mixed loads (denim, towels, blankets together). $360 to $540.</li>
      <li><strong>Thermistor / temperature sensor.</strong> Year 4 to 7 typical wear. $220 to $360.</li>
      <li><strong>Control board (coin/card integration).</strong> Most expensive vended service item, year 5 to 8. $980 to $1,400.</li>
      <li><strong>Door glass cracking.</strong> Vandalism or impact damage. Tempered glass replacement $360 to $640.</li>
      <li><strong>Belt drive system.</strong> High cycle count, year 4 to 6 typical. $340 to $580 belt plus pulley service.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Field observations</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Three things we see on coin laundry calls that aren't in the manual.</h2>

    <p><strong>1. Card-tap migration is faster than most operators planned for.</strong> Five years ago most LA laundromats were straight coin operation. Today most chains have migrated to card-tap (CCI, ESD) or mobile-app payment (PayRange, ShinePay), and the integration with the machine controller is where service complexity sits now. The hardware is reliable but the firmware and configuration are where things break. When a "card reader doesn't work," the diagnostic order is cable, terminal firmware, controller integration, and finally hardware swap. We see about 40% of card-tap calls resolve at firmware or configuration without parts replacement.</p>

    <p><strong>2. Vandalism-prone locations need hardened fixtures, not just better service.</strong> Some LA laundromats see chronic vandalism: door glass cracking, control panel damage, coin slot tampering. Repeat repairs on the same fixture every 3 to 6 months mean the underlying installation isn't right for the location. We discuss hardening options: reinforced control covers, integrated security camera coverage of the fixture, anti-tamper coin slots. Up-front cost runs $400 to $1,200 per machine but eliminates the recurring damage cycle.</p>

    <p><strong>3. Mixed-load lint is the silent killer of vended drain pumps.</strong> Vended laundromat customers run mixed loads (denim, towels, blankets together) that residential users wouldn't. The lint volume per load is 2 to 3x typical residential. Drain pumps that the manufacturer rates for 5-to-7 year life routinely fail at year 3 to 5 in vended service. Quarterly pump-housing cleaning extends pump life meaningfully; we include it in our preventive contracts.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
